34027.name: Table Builder
34027.description:
Table Builder

Table Builder lets you paste tabular data and generates tables from a single component.

For each entry in the spread sheet, Table Builder creates an instance of your original cell component, positions it in a grid and updates the cell's first child of type text with the data entry from the spreadsheet (Excel, Numbers, etc).


Usage

  1. Create a component that contains a text label (as a direct child)
  2. Select an instance of that component
  3. In the plugins menu, open Table Builder
  4. Copy tabular data from the spreadsheet and paste it into the text area of the plugin's UI
  5. Click on the Build Table button

33845.name: SVG to JSX with MUI
33845.description:
SVG to JSX with MUI

This plugin converts selected SVGs to JSX for MUI. And you can download it as zip file.


HOW TO USE

  1. Click the icons you want to convert.
  2. Open plugin and check preview.
  3. Click export


Additional functions will be added. (e.g. disable optimization, without MUI, preview)

33892.description:

  • Figma Color Styles are automatically created from files loaded into Palette Importer
  • An additional â€˜Paste Swatchesâ€™ feature pastes color swatch shapes onto the Figma page
  • Any existing color names and groups contained in the file are retained
  • Individual colors and/or color groups can be toggled on or off to give control over which are included in the import


Instructions

  1. Load a compatible color file format
  2. Preview the colors and groups
  3. Click â€˜Paste Swatchesâ€™ to paste color swatch shapes to the Figma page
  4. Click â€˜Create Color Stylesâ€™ to import the colors into the Color Styles panel


More at fusepilot.com
